4 It's been almost a year & a half since I last ate here, liked it, reviewed it, & gave it 4-Stars, wondering why some people were trashing it.  Well, nothing has changed!  The posted reviews are still all over the place.  I've eaten at many dozens of different Valley Chinese buffets since then, so maybe now I can I finally discern the "One-Starness" of Fuji Buffet & tear it a new one...  or not!  Here goes:  *  I came a little after noon, & joined a cheery, moderate crowd in this big place.  (Were all of them hungry for a 1-Star lunch?  Was it a hundred different people all coincidentally here on their very first visit & not aware of how awful it was going to be?  Come on!)  *  The food selection was huge... 117 items, not counting sauces & dressings!  *  The service was friendly & attentive.  *  Various sizes of plates & bowls to choose from...  a nice touch.  *  Comfortable booth, peaceful ambiance (even with lots of customers),  & excellent restaurant lighting... Front windows thoughtfully decorated to keep daytime glare out.  *  The restaurant looked VERY CLEAN to me, just as last time...  NOT DIRTY (including the bathroom).  *  The moderate selection of Sushi was attractive & tasty.  *  Lots of seafood to choose from, & even some of the chicken dishes were unusual & special!  *  Some REALLY GOOD stuff to lock in that fourth Star included the Buffalo Wings, pork spare ribs, Szechwan Chicken, & various seafood dishes, including "Pork Shrimp".  (This is medium-sized shrimp stuffed with pork sausage & seasoned, then breaded & deep fried.)  It was SO GOOD!!  *  Lots of desserts too, including various flavors of REAL ice cream! ================================================= Here's the worst I can come up with:  *  There's a TV.  (It was playing low).  *  The Hot & Sour Soup wasn't very good.  *  The Cole Slaw was sitting out by the Sushi, at room temperature.  It needs to be COLD to taste right!  *  The spinach was a blah, & little oily.  Ok, so BFD!  Take those things away & there are still 114 dishes that are good to great.  FOUR STARS!!  Lunch Buffet $7.39/$6.65 Sr.
