4 I tried to come to this big place on 9/24 to eat & do an update, & it was closed, out of business, kapoot, with a big chain wrapped around the bars on the front door!  I reported as much to Yelp.  Days later, I contacted Ms. China through a phone number in a note that got taped up to the door that morning.  (Numbers are the same in Chinese!)  She said the place would reopen today, but not as a buffet!  Well, today here it is again, reopened & remodeled somewhat, as...  FUJI BUFFET!  Can you imagine?  Inside, I asked Ms. China if she was the same owner as before & how long it had been closed.  She said yes, same ownership, & that they had been closed for a year.  Now, though, after having just reported all this to Yelp, I see Yelp reviews from just recently!  Obviously they weren't closed a year, & Ms. just made an ass out of me to Yelp!  1 Star!!!  "F" this place!!!  I'm out of here!!!     :-O  Ok, I'll be nice.  Let me start over:  Fuji threw their "Grand Reopening" today at 11 AM after having been closed for a short time, & I ran in through the front door!  (My second Chinese Buffet Grand Opening since yesterday!  Life is good!     :-))  The Sushi bar has been redone completely from the last time I was here, & moved up front.  There is also a Mongolian BBQ now!  They had about 110 food items, not counting sauces & dressings, easily qualifying it as a "Super Buffet".  The table service was lovely, & all the food was good.  There were a few standouts for me, including their fancy, just hand prepared GOURMET Egg Foo Young!!  Yum-a-mundi!!  The thick, battered, fish steaks were exceptional too, as was the fancy pork chop dish.  Excellent new life has been breathed into Fuji here, & it's a high 4 Stars from me.  Just don't believe any answers you get from Ms. China!  She's the middle-aged owner lady you'll see running around in there.  She speaks confidently to you, while wild guessing what you've just asked her!  Weekday Lunch Buffet $7.59/$6.83 Sr.
